<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is represented by a single specimen, in reasonable condition, but anal tube is missing. Small species, 4 mm long and 0.35 mm wide; exact number of chaetigers difficult to establish, but at least 17 counted, although 18 may be present.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body cylindrical and smooth without distinct annulation (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Ophelina cf. abranchiata sp. NHM _ 2017 (specimen NHM _ 2017). A Live image, whole specimen B Lab image, whole specimen (stained,) C Lab image, whole specimen (faded stain) D Lab image, anterior (stained, arrow highlighting dark banding) E Lab image, detail of anterior F Lab image, detail of capillary chaetae. Scale bars: 1 mm (B, C); 100 μm (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350271" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure19">
Fig. 19
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–C">A-C</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
). Preserved specimen yellow in ethanol; live specimen translucent, with yellow gut (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Ophelina cf. abranchiata sp. NHM _ 2017 (specimen NHM _ 2017). A Live image, whole specimen B Lab image, whole specimen (stained,) C Lab image, whole specimen (faded stain) D Lab image, anterior (stained, arrow highlighting dark banding) E Lab image, detail of anterior F Lab image, detail of capillary chaetae. Scale bars: 1 mm (B, C); 100 μm (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350271" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure19">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
). Ventral and lateral grooves distinct along whole length of body. Anterior and posterior-most chaetigers slightly shorter than mid-body chaetigers.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.883.36193.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350271" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 19" startId="F19">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 19.</emphasis>
